                  <Text layoutX="36.0" layoutY="437.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The COVID-19 pandemic has taken the world by storm and resulted in various aspects of our lives being immensely affected by the consequences of the spread of the virus. The global economy has also been a victim of the coronavirus outbreak since a recession is about to take place. Medicine is not the only field of science that has been actively taking part in the fight against the coronavirus. Whether it’s Engineering or Computer Sciences, all disciplines of sciences are playing a role in helping the world with the state that it is in. For that reason, the team has taken the responsibility of using all the techniques and valuable information that is being learned in the CSC311 course to take part in tackling a real-life global scale problem such as the coronavirus epidemic by developing a COVID-19 Information System using Java." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="646.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="36.0" AnchorPane.rightAnchor="38.0">
