                  <Text layoutX="36.0" layoutY="764.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="In this project, we aim to use a graphical user interface to implement what we have learned in the ‘Java Programming for the Internet’ course and apply it to our project which will be about creating or designing a COVID-19 information system; the system we aim to design should have the main information such as the total number of cases, the number of infected per day and the total number of recovered. We also aim to make our application be as accurate as possible about the information by making the application refresh frequently to ensure the information is updated more often. The main objectives we are trying to achieve is to use as many methods and features that we learned in this course and implement them in our design; we would also like to achieve a userfriendly design that is simple and easy to interact with. By the end of our design we hope that it would help whoever uses it to be updated regularly about information regarding the spread of COVID-19." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="646.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="36.0" AnchorPane.rightAnchor="38.0">
